{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/monzo-users/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/2a50e/monzo-users.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=\\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\'%20width=\\'400\\'%20height=\\'256\\'%3e%3cpath%20d=\\'M20%2014l-1%20109c0%20119-1%20109%206%20109l3%201c1%201%2035%202%20167%202a1422%201422%200%2000181-3c3%200%204%200%205-3V13H201L20%2014\\'%20fill=\\'%23d3d3d3\\'%20fill-rule=\\'evenodd\\'/%3e%3c/svg%3e'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/ba381/monzo-users.webp 200w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/7f61c/monzo-users.webp 400w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/d00b9/monzo-users.webp 800w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/92f8c/monzo-users.webp 1200w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/fad48/monzo-users.webp 1600w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/f3c66/monzo-users.webp 2352w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/772e8/monzo-users.png 200w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/e17e5/monzo-users.png 400w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/5a190/monzo-users.png 800w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/c1b63/monzo-users.png 1200w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/29007/monzo-users.png 1600w,\n/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/2a50e/monzo-users.png 2352w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/5a190/monzo-users.png\"\n          alt=\"Monzo Users\"\n          title=\"Monzo Users\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"monzo.com\" title=\"Monzo\">Monzo</a> is a digital \"challenger\" bank from the UK.</p>\n<p>I thought it would be interesting to use GitHub to automatically update and store data regarding the growth of Monzo's current account user numbers.</p>\n<p>Since their website includes an auto updating tally of users, I just found the api and the python scripts utilise this.</p>\n<p>Similar to the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"/projects/predictions/\" title=\"COVID-19 infection predictions\">COVID-19 infection predictions</a>, this uses GitHub actions to automatically update and store data regarding the growth of Monzo's current account user numbers.\nIt also builds a <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://jamesjarvis.github.io/monzo-users\" title=\"simple react webpage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">simple react webpage</a> to display the data in a graph.\nOr, if you prefer you can download <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jamesjarvis/monzo-users/master/monzo_users.csv\" title=\"the data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">the data</a> for yourself.</p>\n<p>Feel free to make a PR if you have some data that can fill in the gaps.</p>\n<p>Some (better) visualisations can be found here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://bankstats.joecarter.xyz/d/000000001/monzo-current-acc?orgId=1&refresh=5m&from=now-1y&to=now\" title=\"Grafana current account growth\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Grafana current account growth</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://grafana.tombowdit.ch/d/AWZDPrYik/monzo?orgId=2&refresh=30m&from=now-6M&to=now\" title=\"Another, grafana approach\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Another, grafana approach</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"is a digital \"challenger\" bank from the UK. I thought it would be interesting to use GitHub to automatically update and store data regarding the growth of Monzo's current account user numbers. Since…","frontmatter":{"title":"📈 Graphing Monzo Growth","date":"March, 2020","tech":["Python","React"],"link":"https://jamesjarvis.github.io/monzo-users/","source":"https://github.com/jamesjarvis/monzo-users","previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/19779e011946c2ea1c01288b725ac24f/f3583/monzo-users.png","height":768,"width":1200}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/monzo-users/"}}}